# Never Clip Or Cut Off Text

This is a critical rule for this project.

## Core rule

- Never clip or cut off text.
- Never set `overflow: hidden` on any container that holds text unless you are 100% certain the text will never be clipped.
- Add `overflow: visible` to text containers by default.

## Auto-fitting / FitLine

- When using FitLine or any auto-fitting typography component, add a width safety buffer of at least `0.97` as the scale multiplier so wide characters at the end of a word are never cut off.
- Treat words like `NESPRESSO` as a required edge case, especially wide ending characters such as `S`, `O`, `M`, and `W`.

## Container sizing

- Never constrain a text container to a fixed width without also checking that the text fits fully inside it.
- If a crop, mask, transform, or fit calculation risks trimming glyphs, expand the visible area or reduce the fit target until every character clears the edge.

## Required checks

- Check long words.
- Check wide characters: `S`, `O`, `M`, `W`.
- Check words that sit at the end of a line.
- Check both top/bottom and left/right edges before considering the work done.
